18/01/2005
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Prime Minister Ferenc Gyurcsany pledged intensified support for Romania's bid to join the EU in 2007, during talks with Romanian counterpart Calin Popescu Tariceanu in Budapest on Monday (17 January).
They agreed that their governments should hold annual joint meetings aimed at enhancing bilateral ties and assisting Romania's efforts to implement EU-related reforms.
The first session is planned for the autumn.
In other news, Romanian President Traian Basescu's office announced on Monday that he would pay an official visit to Britain on 31 January.
It would be Basescu's first visit abroad since taking office last month.
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 18/01/05;
Reuters - 17/01/05)
